  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "34. people took … their kneading-troughs—Having lived so long in Egypt, they must have been in the habit of using the utensils common in that country. The Egyptian kneading-trough was a bowl of wicker or rush work, and it admitted of being hastily wrapped up with the dough in it and slung over the shoulder in their hykes or loose upper garments.",
        "children": []
      }
