  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 34.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The people took their dough",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". They probably regarded dough as more convenient for a journey than flour, and so made their flour into dough before starting; but they had no time to add leaven. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Their kneading-troughs",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This rendering is correct, both here and in the two other places where the word occurs (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 8:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 28:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Kneading-troughs would be a necessity in the desert, and, if like those of the modern Arabs, which are merely small wooden bowls, would be light and portable. The dough and kneading-troughs, with perhaps other necessaries, were carried, as the Arabs still carry many small objects, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "bound up in their clothes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "beged",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or ample shawl) upon their shoulders. Exodus 12:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
